             was indicted for <rs id="t18310908-358-off1834" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-off1834" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-off1834" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310908-358-cd1835" type="crimeDate">11th of September</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-358-off1834 t18310908-358-cd1835"></join>, 1 pair of sheets, value 2l.; 3 table-cloths, value 22s.; 1 night-gown, value 3s.; 1 pair of stockings, value 3s.; 1 shirt, value 10s.; 1 cravat, value 2s., and 3 towels, value 1s., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18310908-358-victim2553" type="victimName">
                           Wesley 
                           Doyle
                        <interp inst="t18310908-358-victim2553" type="surname" value="Doyle"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18310908-358-victim2553" type="given" value="Wesley"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18310908-358-victim2553" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , <rs id="t18310908-358-viclabel1836" type="occupation">Esq.</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-358-victim2553 t18310908-358-viclabel1836"></join>; 4 knives, value 1s.; 7 forks, value 1s.; 1 pair of sheets, value 20s.; 1 table-cloth, value 4s.; 1 portmanteau, value 4s.; 2 tea-pots, value 1s.; 1 quilt, value 3s.; 2 pairs of shoes, value 2s.; 1 basin, value 1s., and 1 piece of green baize, value 2s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18310908-358-victim2555" type="victimName">
                     Sarah Esther 
                     Ricketts
                  <interp inst="t18310908-358-victim2555" type="surname" value="Ricketts"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-victim2555" type="given" value="Sarah Esther"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-victim2555" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , her mistress.</p>

               <p>SARAH 
               <persName id="t18310908-358-person2556">
                  ESTHER 
                  RICKETTS
               <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2556" type="surname" value="RICKETTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2556" type="given" value="ESTHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2556" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came to assist her niece, who was my servant, about a fortnight before the Coronation. On the 11th of September my daughter was going to the larder, and saw a band-box of linen, belonging to Captain Doyle, on the stairs; I brought it<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183109080150"></xptr>down, and said to the prisoner, "Is this your's?" she said, "It is;" Captain Doyle directly said it was his, and an officer was called in.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-358-person2557">
                  SARAH 
                  ESTHER RICKETTS
               <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2557" type="surname" value="ESTHER RICKETTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2557" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2557" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutrix's daughter. I saw the things on the stairs; I heard Captain 
               <persName id="t18310908-358-person2558">Doyle</persName>
             say the articles were his - I turned up the bed, and some her things were found; her niece wished her to come to our house; the prisoner said if my mother offered her any wages she should be offended - my mother said she should not think of her being there without being paid; she was called cook.</p>
               <p>CAPTAIN WESLEY DOYLE. I lodge at this house, in Southampton-row. These articles, which were found in the box, are mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-358-person2559">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WILSON
               <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2559" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2559" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2559" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner, and went with a boy to her lodgings - I found there a bundle, containing this bed-quilt and a duplicate of a pair of sheets; I found a few bits of gold on the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-358-person2560">
                  ROBERT 
                  BERSENT
               <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2560" type="surname" value="BERSENT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2560" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-person2560" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in King's Head-court. The prisoner took my parlour about six weeks before the officer came with my apprentice, whom I had sent to the prisoner; I saw the articles found, which her niece had brought in a basket.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. On the Sunday night I was sent for some rum - when I came back, my niece asked where Mrs. Ricketts was; I said, "In the bed-room, looking over the linen."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-358-verdict1837" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-verdict1837" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 44. - <rs id="t18310908-358-punish1838" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-358-punish1838" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-358-defend2551 t18310908-358-punish1838"></join>
               Transported for Fourteen Years
            </rs>.</p>
